Center: US National Nuclear Data Center, Brookhaven, USA
title: Mass and energy distributions in the spontaneous fission of some heavy isotopes

x4freetext: Mass and energy distributions in the spontaneous
fission of some heavy isotopes

x4codes.hlp: University of California, Berkeley, CA, United States of America

x4freetext: Two back-to-back phosphorus-disused guard-ring-
type silicon semiconductor counters.
Transcurium isotopes were produced by long-time
irradiation of curium isotopes with neutrons. The
elements were separated on ion-exchange columns. The
isolated and purified isotopes were electrodeposited
on approximately 5-mu-in.-thick Ni foils.
